1. Ijude *ne bi trebalo* zanemarivati u svakodnevnom životu. (The opinion of others *should not be* neglected in everyday life.)
2. Neki ljudi su skloni da *preuveličavaju* važnost ijuda. (Some people are prone to *exaggerating* the importance of others' opinions.)
3. Moramo biti pažljivi kome dajemo *značaj* i koliko uticaja ijude imaju na nas. (We must be careful about who we give *importance* to and how much influence others' opinions have on us.)
4. Na kraju dana, naša *lična sreća* treba da bude prioritet, a ne zadovoljavanje ijuda. (At the end of the day, our *personal happiness* should be a priority, not pleasing others.)
5. Ne želim da živim svoj život po *meri* ijuda. (I don't want to live my life according to others' *standards*.)
6. Ijude mogu biti korisni kada tražimo *savet* ili *mišljenje* o nečemu. (Others' opinions can be helpful when we seek *advice* or *feedback* on something.)
7. Nije u redu da se neko oseća *manje vrednim* zbog mišljenja ijuda. (It's not okay for someone to feel *less worthy* because of others' opinions.)
8. Važno je razlikovati između konstruktivne kritike i *negativne kritike* od strane ijuda. (It's important to distinguish between constructive criticism and *negative criticism* from others.)